                     </persName>
                     
                  ; and that the said John McGrath had before been convicted of felony
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-208-person1793">
                  GEORGE 
                  POWELL
               <interp inst="t18301209-208-person1793" type="surname" value="POWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-208-person1793" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-208-person1793" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. On the 16th of November, I was opposite Mr. Wilcoxon's who is a <rs id="t18301209-208-viclabel1162" type="occupation">boot and shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-208-victim1792 t18301209-208-viclabel1162"></join> - I saw the two prisoners and another <rs id="t18301209-208-deflabel1163" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-208-defend1788 t18301209-208-deflabel1163"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-208-defend1790 t18301209-208-deflabel1163"></join> together; I saw McGrath take a pair of shoes from the window of the shop, and give them to McCarthy, who rolled them in his apron and walked away with them - McGrath then joined the other lad, and they walked on; I crossed over, and pushed McGrath into a shop - I then followed McCarthy down a turning, and took him; I found these shoes in the apron on the wheel of a cart down the turning.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-208-person1794">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PARDY
               <interp inst="t18301209-208-person1794" type="surname" value="PARDY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-208-person1794" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-208-person1794" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Ralph Wilcoxon - these are his shoes.</p>
               <p>McCarthy's Defence. I saw them laying against a shop - Mr. Powell came and said, "Give me the shoes you stole;" I said I had none - I then put them on the wheel of a cart, and he took them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-208-person1795">
                  GEORGE 
                  POWELL
               <interp inst="t18301209-208-person1795" type="surname" value="POWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-208-person1795" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-208-person1795" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have a certificate from Mr. Clark's office, of the conviction of McGrath, on the 28th of October, in the first year of his present Majesty's reign, for stealing a hat, value 5s., for which he was ordered to be<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183012090102"></xptr>whipped - I attended the trial, and know he is the same person.</p>
               <p>McGRATH - <rs id="t18301209-208-verdict1164" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18301209-208-verdict1164" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 10.</p>
